<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Chamberlain" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Chamberlain,</orth> 1) the officer charged with the direction and management of the private apartments of the king: <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 77</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 77</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.114" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 4, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 4, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h8 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 13</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.7.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 7, 63</bibl>. <cit><quote>thinkest that the bleak air, thy boisterous c., will put thy shirt on warm,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.222" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 222</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a servant who has the care of the chambers in an inn: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 52</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>